==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mammillated
<hw>Mam"mil*la`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Mammilla</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having small nipples, or small protuberances like
nipples or mammae.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Bounded like a nipple; -- said of
the apex of some shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mammilliform</ent>⟦br⟧
